<Link id="l00026" /><CodeLine lineNumber="26"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// A simple intrusive list implementation.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00027" /><CodeLine lineNumber="27"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00028" /><CodeLine lineNumber="28"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// This is a simple intrusive list for a \\c T that inherits from \\c</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00029" /><CodeLine lineNumber="29"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// ilist&#95;node&lt;T&gt;.  The list never takes ownership of anything inserted in it.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00030" /><CodeLine lineNumber="30"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00031" /><CodeLine lineNumber="31"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Unlike \\a iplist&lt;T&gt; and \\a ilist&lt;T&gt;, \\a simple&#95;ilist&lt;T&gt; never deletes</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00032" /><CodeLine lineNumber="32"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// values, and has no callback traits.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00033" /><CodeLine lineNumber="33"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00034" /><CodeLine lineNumber="34"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The API for adding nodes include \\a push&#95;front(), \\a push&#95;back(), and \\a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00035" /><CodeLine lineNumber="35"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// insert().  These all take values by reference (not by pointer), except for</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00036" /><CodeLine lineNumber="36"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// the range version of \\a insert().</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00037" /><CodeLine lineNumber="37"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00038" /><CodeLine lineNumber="38"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// There are three sets of API for discarding nodes from the list: \\a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00039" /><CodeLine lineNumber="39"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// remove(), which takes a reference to the node to remove, \\a erase(), which</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00040" /><CodeLine lineNumber="40"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// takes an iterator or iterator range and returns the next one, and \\a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00041" /><CodeLine lineNumber="41"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// clear(), which empties out the container.  All three are constant time</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00042" /><CodeLine lineNumber="42"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// operations.  None of these deletes any nodes; in particular, if there is a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00043" /><CodeLine lineNumber="43"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// single node in the list, then these have identical semantics:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00044" /><CodeLine lineNumber="44"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\li \\c L.remove(L.front());</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00045" /><CodeLine lineNumber="45"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\li \\c L.erase(L.begin());</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00046" /><CodeLine lineNumber="46"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\li \\c L.clear();</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00047" /><CodeLine lineNumber="47"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00048" /><CodeLine lineNumber="48"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// As a convenience for callers, there are parallel APIs that take a \\c</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00049" /><CodeLine lineNumber="49"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Disposer (such as \\c std::default&#95;delete&lt;T&gt;): \\a removeAndDispose(), \\a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00050" /><CodeLine lineNumber="50"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// eraseAndDispose(), and \\a clearAndDispose().  These have different names</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00051" /><CodeLine lineNumber="51"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// because the extra semantic is otherwise non-obvious.  They are equivalent</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00052" /><CodeLine lineNumber="52"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// to calling \\a std::for&#95;each() on the range to be discarded.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00053" /><CodeLine lineNumber="53"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00054" /><CodeLine lineNumber="54"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The currently available \\p Options customize the nodes in the list.  The</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00055" /><CodeLine lineNumber="55"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// same options must be specified in the \\a ilist&#95;node instantiation for</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00056" /><CodeLine lineNumber="56"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// compatibility (although the order is irrelevant).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00057" /><CodeLine lineNumber="57"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\li Use \\a ilist&#95;tag to designate which ilist&#95;node for a given \\p T this</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00058" /><CodeLine lineNumber="58"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// list should use.  This is useful if a type \\p T is part of multiple,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00059" /><CodeLine lineNumber="59"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// independent lists simultaneously.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00060" /><CodeLine lineNumber="60"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\li Use \\a ilist&#95;sentinel&#95;tracking to always (or never) track whether a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00061" /><CodeLine lineNumber="61"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// node is a sentinel.  Specifying \\c true enables the \\a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00062" /><CodeLine lineNumber="62"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// ilist&#95;node::isSentinel() API.  Unlike \\a ilist&#95;node::isKnownSentinel(),</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00063" /><CodeLine lineNumber="63"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// which is only appropriate for assertions, \\a ilist&#95;node::isSentinel() is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00064" /><CodeLine lineNumber="64"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// appropriate for real logic.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00065" /><CodeLine lineNumber="65"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00066" /><CodeLine lineNumber="66"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Here are examples of \\p Options usage:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00067" /><CodeLine lineNumber="67"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\li \\c simple&#95;ilist&lt;T&gt; gives the defaults.  \\li \\c</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00068" /><CodeLine lineNumber="68"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// simple&#95;ilist&lt;T,ilist&#95;sentinel&#95;tracking&lt;true&gt;&gt; enables the \\a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00069" /><CodeLine lineNumber="69"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// ilist&#95;node::isSentinel() API.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00070" /><CodeLine lineNumber="70"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\li \\c simple&#95;ilist&lt;T,ilist&#95;tag&lt;A&gt;,ilist&#95;sentinel&#95;tracking&lt;false&gt;&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00071" /><CodeLine lineNumber="71"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// specifies a tag of A and that tracking should be off (even when</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00072" /><CodeLine lineNumber="72"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// LLVM&#95;ENABLE&#95;ABI&#95;BREAKING&#95;CHECKS are enabled).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00073" /><CodeLine lineNumber="73"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// \\li \\c simple&#95;ilist&lt;T,ilist&#95;sentinel&#95;tracking&lt;false&gt;,ilist&#95;tag&lt;A&gt;&gt; is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00074" /><CodeLine lineNumber="74"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// equivalent to the last.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00075" /><CodeLine lineNumber="75"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
